snippet: Mayor Bill de Blasio says he is a fan, but he was not among the 4.8 million visitors the park attracted last year. In fact, he has never been there.
abstract: Mayor Bill de Blasio has yet to visit New York City's High Line park, which attracted some 4.8 million visitors in 2013; absence is in stark contrast to predecessor Michael R Bloomberg, who championed park and poured millions of his own dollars into it; park has attracted string of luxury buildings to Manhattan's Far West Side and is perhaps a symbol of the gentrification that de Blasio has so consistently denounced.
lead_paragraph: Mayor Bill de Blasio says he is a fan, but he was not among the 4.8 million visitors the park attracted last year. In fact, he has never been there.

headline.main: High Line Draws Millions, but de Blasio Isn’t One
headline.print_headline: High Line Draws Millions, but the Mayor Isn’t One
